subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen with six ventrites (
Fig. 4
). Abdominal postcoxal lines recurved roundly but incomplete, without additional line (
Fig. 4
). Apical margin of ventrite 5 truncate; ventrite 6 rounded, emarginate (
Fig. 5
); apodeme of male sternum IX rod-like, thin. Tergite X large, transverse, truncate at apex (
Fig. 10
).

Male genitalia
(
Figs. 7–10
). Basal piece devoid of spines, penis guide symmetrical, slightly longer than parameres, very broad, broadening from base to apex, leaf-like, suddenly narrowing at apex to a pointed process, excised (
Figs. 7, 8
). Parameres well developed, apically simple, covered with hairs (
Figs. 7, 8
). Penis long, broad, with membranous apical process; penis base with both arms reduced (
Fig. 9
).

Distribution. India : Arunachal Pradesh (Tawang), Sikkim , West Bengal (Darjeeling; this paper); Nepal ( Kapur 1963 ; Canepari 1986 ; Miyatake 1967 ;
Das et al. 2020
).
